criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Post-comatose patients ;

          -  Patients in vegetative state/unresponsive wakefulness syndrome or in minimally
             conscious state ;

          -  Patients with stable condition (including vita signs) ;

          -  Patients with cerebral lesion resulting from a known etiology ;

          -  Patients with intact skin at the stimulation site.

          -  Patients < 21 days after the acute brain injury

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnant patients ;

          -  Patients with a cerebral shunt ;

          -  Patients with an active implant (i.e. pacemaker)

          -  Patient with premorbid neurology antecedent

          -  Patients in coma
